(cpi, power_memory).explanation: Memory power consumption affects CPI because higher memory power often correlates with more memory accesses and longer memory latencies, which increase the cycles needed per instruction;

(cpi, power).explanation: Total power consumption influences CPI as higher power usage typically indicates more active components and potentially longer execution times, leading to more cycles per instruction;

(cpi, power_pad).explanation: Pad power consumption is related to I/O interface power and has no direct causal relationship with the cycles per instruction metric;
